superMiscConds.notes: Pay restitution, to be determined, by restitution hearing, to be referred to Court Commissioner, to be scheduled at a future date.**01-31-18 /s/TTF approved $5,000.00 restitution is determined.**

Defendant is required to authorize the department to collect funds from the defendant's wages and from other moneys held in the defendant's prisoner's account to be used for payment of obligations in reasonable amounts as determined by DOC. If any fines, costs, surcharges, & restitution remain outstanding at the end of the confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining balances shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil Judgment will be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

No contact with anyone under the age of 18 without DOC and agent approval.
No contact direct/indirect with any victims or their pseudonyms.
No use of a computer type device which has the potential of internet connectivity.

Not eligible for challenge incarceration
Not eligible for earned release program
No DNA Surcharge due to age of charges.
DNA to be in databank for future reference.
Complete programming as deemed appropriate by the Compas assessment and the Department of Corrections.
Register as a sex offender and fully cooperate with the Sex Offender Registry.
**Under Wis. Stat. 939.615(3), the lifetime supervision shall begin upon the discharge from extended supervision. /s/TTF 06-18-18**
